PITSO Mosimane has admitted his fears about the "monster" he helped create at Mamelodi Sundowns. The Al Ahly coach dismantled his former side as the Egyptian giants put one foot in the Caf Champions League semi-finals with a 2-0 win in Cairo on Saturday. “I had sleepless nights about Mamelodi Sundowns,” Mosimane revealed. “I watched seven of their games and just kept quiet and kept focus. God is there to help us with the results. This tie still has a heartbeat. Sundowns can still turn it around.     